This is a small solver for the puzzle board game “Par Odin!”. It explores the
solution space by brute-forcing all possible configurations until it finds a 
solution.

## What it does

- **Models the rules of the game** so that a board state can be represented and
  evaluated programmatically.
- **Searches the solution space** using an algorithm that prunes impossible
  branches early, keeping the solver reasonably fast for typical boards.
- **Outputs concrete solutions**, making it easier to verify results or explore
  alternative layouts for tricky puzzles.

It turns what can be a painstaking manual process into something closer to an
interactive exploration tool. It also removes all fun from the game, so you’ve
been warned.

## Why I built it

Par Odin! Solver started as a way to combine a puzzle I enjoy with an interest
in algorithms and state search. Encoding the game rules surfaced plenty of
edge‑cases and was a fun exercise in balancing correctness with performance.

The repository contains usage instructions, board representations and examples
if you want to try solving your own “Par Odin!” setups.

